## Other information

Existing tests did *not* like this change since it required updating basically every compliance test which included i18n, so most of the PR is just fixing them. Unfortunately, the existing parser for objects in `__i18n*__` macros for tests expects an object with a maximum depth of only one (`{foo: 'bar'}`), while tests containing `original_code` go as deep as *six* (`{foo: {bar: {baz: {...}}}}`). This is compounded by the fact that Angular template evaluation also uses `{{ foo }}` which adds to the depth even though they are in string literals. I updated the object param regular expression to support a maximum of six levels of nesting in the object, which is good enough for now. Longer term we should really replace the system with a proper parser.

